  "title": "Operation Coordinator (Up $3900)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location: Woodlands</strong><br /><strong>Mon to Fri 8.30am to 5.30pm</strong><br /><strong>Salary: $3000-$3900</strong><br /><strong>Have AWS & Bonus</strong><br /><strong></strong></p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong><br /><br /><u><strong>Production Scheduling</strong></u></p><p><p><p>Develop and maintain production schedules based on customer orders, forecasts, and inventory levels.<br />Coordinate with Sales, Purchasing, Engineering, QA, and Production to ensure timely availability of materials and capacity</p></p><p><p><br /><br /><u><strong>Material Planning & Inventory Control</strong></u></p></p><p><p>Ensure all raw materials, components, and tools are available on time to meet production needs.<br />Work closely with store/logistics teams to monitor stock levels and avoid shortages or overstocking.<br /><br /><br /><u><strong>Order Tracking & Status Updates</strong></u></p></p><p>Monitor work orders and ensure timely completion of production jobs.</p><p><p>Update stakeholders on production progress and address any delays or issues<br /></p><p><br /><u><strong>Communication & Coordination</strong></u></p></p><p><p>Act as the liaison between production floor, quality, logistics, and customer service.</p><p>Resolve conflicts in schedules, material constraints, or unexpected machine downtime.</p></p><p><p>Maintain accurate records of production plans, work orders, and changes.</p></p><p><p>Generate reports for management on production output, efficiency, and delivery performance.<br /></p><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Requirements</strong><br />NITEC/Diploma/Bachelor's Degree<br />Working experiences in manufacturing sector preferred<br /></p></p></p><p><u><strong>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></u>\nPlease submit your updated resume in MS format by using the <strong>APPLY NOW BUTTON.</strong><br />\nAlternatively, you may also email your resume to us at <a href=\"mailto:emily.fong@atomrecruit.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>emily.fong@atomrecruit.com</strong></a></p><p><strong>Emily Fong</strong>\n<strong>Senior Talent Specialist</strong>\nAtomrecruit Pte. Ltd. | MOM EA License No.: 15C7443\nEA Personnel Reg No.: R1768368</p>",
